```

In this example, the `encodeString` function takes a long string and returns its Base64 encoded version, while the `decodeString` function takes the Base64 encoded string and returns the original long string.

Keep in mind that Base64 encoding will increase the length of the string, but it will be much shorter than the original long string. The encoded string will be URL-safe, meaning it can be used in URLs without any issues.

